sql:
SELECT SUM(download_count) AS total_downloads
FROM library_versions
WHERE library_id = 0;

SELECT MAX(download_count) AS max_downloads
FROM library_versions
WHERE library_id = 0;

SELECT version_number
  FROM library_versions
  WHERE library_id = 0;

SELECT COUNT(*) AS active_doc_count
FROM documentation
WHERE library_id = 1 AND status = 'active';

external_knowledge:
- Top 5 refers to the libraries with the highest total interaction counts in each section, as per the ROW_NUMBER() function;
- Interactions include views, downloads, and forks;
- Stars and forks refer to the number of stars and forks the library has on its repository.
